== Research
Research Assistant, *The Snow Lab* (Co-PIs: [https://www.gse.harvard.edu/faculty/catherine-snow Prof. Catherine E. Snow], [https://www.gse.harvard.edu/faculty/si-chen Dr. Si Chen], [https://www.gse.harvard.edu/faculty/junlei-li Dr. Junlei Li]), Aug 2019 - present \n
~~~
[http://veec.cdrf.org.cn/index.html One Village One Preschool (OVOP) Project] \n 
OVOP is a government-supported public intervention launched by the [https://www.cdrf.org.cn/ China Development Research Foundation] in collaboration with Professor Catherine E. Snow, which provided disadvantaged rural and minority children in central and western rural China with access to early childhood education (ECE). OVOP has established about 2300 centers in ten provinces, enrolling over 170,000 3–6-year olds, free of charge for all. This project is one of the [https://www.wise-qatar.org/project/one-village-one-preschool-china/ World Innovation Summit for Education (WISE) Awards winners].\n
~~~

- Carried out an independent study on the relationship between shared book reading strategies & children’s language development, transcribed & coded video according to self-developed coding scheme; analyzed & visualized data by Stata
- Conducted literature review of the academic & social outcomes of early childhood education, topics include picture book reading strategies, classroom organization, child development of vocabulary & social-emotional skills, the use of iPad & other technologies
- Designed researched-based teaching plans & classroom activities for 80+ OVOP classrooms in Yunnan & Sichuan Provinces, co-authored handbooks for teachers & students during the pandemic \n

Research Intern, [https://reacheveryreader.gse.harvard.edu/ *Reach Every Reader*] (PI: [https://www.gse.harvard.edu/faculty/joseph-blatt Joseph Blatt]), Jan 2020 - Jul 2020 \n
- Designed a study on whether parent-child conversations conducted through a smart speaker are beneficial and enjoyable for the child, while also serving to promote oral language and pre-literacy skills
- Conducted literature on quality & quantity of parent-child interaction in low-income households, the role of intelligent devices (iPad, Alexa, TV, mobile phones, etc.) in home settings, child development of language & literacy
- Designed questionnaires and interview questions (to be continued) 
- Completed the Institutional Review Board (IRB) protocol and was approved by IRB
- Collaborated with other RER project teams, incl. literacy assessment, teacher professional development, & elementary school reading performance.


